  "decision_conditions": [
    "Condition : 1 - The work to which this consent relates shall be begun not later than three years from the date of this consent. \r\nReason: To comply with the requirements of Section 18 of the Planning (Listed Buildings and Conservation Areas) Act 1990, Section 51 of the Planning and Compulsory Purchase Act 2004 and the Town and Country Planning (Development Management Procedure) (England) Order 2015.\r\n",
    "Condition : 2 - The works of demolition/alteration hereby authorised shall be carried out in complete accordance with the following plans and specifications:\r\n8651/ EX-00 Rev A, 651/ PL-01, 8651/ PL-02 Rev A, 8651/ PL-03, 8651/ PL-04, 8651/ PL-05, 8651/ PL-06, 8651/ PL-07, 8651/ PL-08 Rev A, 8651/ PL-09 Rev B, 8651/ PL-10.\r\nReason: To safeguard the character of the building, in accordance with Council policy LP3 of the Local Plan.\r\n",
    "Condition : 3 - Prior to internal alterations to the listed building (excluding external demolition works), detailed information of the protection of the building and of the internal alterations shall be submitted to and approved by the local planning authority.  Such details shall include:\r\n-\tConstruction method statement detailing the method of protection of all historic features within the building during the works of conversion and alteration. This includes the staircases, which are to be retained unaltered, fireplaces, alcoves, friezes, cornicing, ceilings, skirting, doors and architraves and any other historic features or fabric.\r\n-\tDetails of location and reinstatement of missing/incomplete cornicing and decorative friezes to be reinstated and repaired.\r\n-\tStatement detailing each of the doors to be moved and their new location within the building. \r\n-\tDetails of service runs for drainage for the pods to be added to each room. \r\nThe development shall be constructed in accordance with the approved details and retained as such.\r\nReason: To ensure a high quality of development and to accord with policies LP1 and LP3 of the Local Plan coupled with the requirements of the National Planning Policy Framework.\r\n",
    "Condition : 4 - REASON FOR GRANTING LISTED BUILDING CONSENT \r\nThe Council has had regard to local development plan policies, to any representations received and to other material planning considerations. The following policies were considered relevant to the grant of planning permission: \r\n- Local Plan (2023) policy LP3 historic environment \r\nThe proposal has been granted permission for the following reasons: \r\nThe proposal would not harm the significance of the Grade II listed building or its settings, thereby according with policy LP3 and Section 66 of the Planning (Listed Buildings and Conservation Areas) Act 1990 and the NPPF.\r\n",
    "Condition : 5 - INFORMATIVE: The applicant undertook a comprehensive photographic study of the exterior and the interior of the building as it currently exists. These are of high significance in the context of the history of the building and the photographs should be deposited in the appropriate Historic Environment Record locally, namely Battersea Local History Library, and with the Historic England HER. "
  ],
